INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4000','letter','1777-03-01','Middlebrook','NJ','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','I have taken the liberty to trouble you with this hint, as sometimes things the most obvious escape attention. If you agree with me in sentiment, you will easily fall upon the most proper mode for answering the purpose.','ltr_gwa4000.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4001','letter','1779-04-14','Middlebrook','NJ','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','The circumstance of which you have obliged me with a communication, is among a number of other instances of the unfriendly views which have governed a certain gentleman from a very early period.','ltr_gwa4001.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4002','letter','1779-04-00','Middlebrook','NJ','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','If, under this sanction, I should step beyond the line you would wish to draw, and suggest ideas or ask questions which are improper to be answered, you hare only to pass them by in silence.','ltr_gwa4002.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4003','letter','1779-05-10','Middlebrook','NJ','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','To me it appears that our affairs are in a very delicate situation ; and what is not the least to be lamented is, that many people think they are in a very flourishing way ; and seem in a great measure insensible to the danger with which we are threatened.','ltr_gwa4003.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4004','letter','1779-10-07','West Point','NY','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','Among the number of your friends, permit me also to congratulate you, and my country, on your late honourable and important appointment.','ltr_gwa4004.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4005','letter','1782-10-18','Verplancks Point','NY','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','We have now passed another campaign, and no very important occurrence has intervened on this side the Atlantic.','ltr_gwa4005.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4006','letter','1785-09-27','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','It gave me great pleasure to hear of your appointment as secretary of the United States for the department of foreign affairs ; a happier choice in my opinion could not have been made','ltr_gwa4006.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4007','letter','1788-09-03','Mount Vernon','VA','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','With peculiar pleasure I now congratulate you on the success of your labours to obtain an unconditional ratification of the proposed constitution in the Convention of your State','ltr_gwa4007.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4008','letter','1791-09-04','Philadelphia','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','The indisposition, and consequent absence from Mount Vernon, of my nephew, Major Washington, to whom the care of my private business is intrusted, makes it indispensably necessary for me to go home before the meeting of Congress.','ltr_gwa4008.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4009','letter','1794-08-30','Philadelphia','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','On this irregular and high-handed proceeding of Mr. Simcoe, which is no longer masked, I would rather hear what the ministry of Great Britain will say, than pronounce my own sentiments thereon.','ltr_gwa4009.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4010','letter','1794-11-01','Philadelphia','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','That the self-created societies which have spread themselves over this country, have been labouring incessantly to sow the seeds of distrust, jealousy, and of course discontent, thereby hoping to effect some revolution in the government, is not unknown to you.','ltr_gwa4010.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4011','letter','1794-12-18','Philadelphia','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','As I expected, and as you have been informed the result would probably be, so it has happened, that the western insurrection has terminated highly honourable for this country','ltr_gwa4011.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4012','letter','1795-09-31','Philadelphia','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','You will have learned from the public gazettes, and through other more authentic channels, that all that rested with me to do, to give ratification to the treaty between this country and Great Britain, is already accomplished.','ltr_gwa4012.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4013','letter','1795-12-21','Philadelphia','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','My information with respect to the general disposition of the people, accords with yours; and I have little doubt of a perfect amelioration of sentiment, alter the present fermentation (which is not only subsiding, but changing) has evaporated a little more.','ltr_gwa4013.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4014','letter','1796-03-31','Philadelphia','PA','US','George','Washington','','John','Jay','','individual','','The purport of it is pleasing ; but the conduct of the British armed vessels in the West Indies is intolerable beyond all forbearance.','ltr_gwa4014.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
